WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:13.540 --> 00:00:15.507
King Uther.
there is a visitor.

3
00:00:15.542 --> 00:00:17.776
She won't give her name.

4
00:00:28.521 --> 00:00:32.591
Who are you?

5
00:00:37.297 --> 00:00:38.931
Morgan.

6
00:00:38.965 --> 00:00:41.366
Father.

7
00:00:43.470 --> 00:00:44.937
Your whore still lives.

8
00:00:50.143 --> 00:00:51.543
You'll respect your mother.

9
00:00:51.578 --> 00:00:54.012
Stepmother.

10
00:00:55.415 --> 00:00:57.449
Why are you here?

11
00:00:57.484 --> 00:01:02.120
I've come home and I
want to offer you forgiveness.

12
00:01:02.155 --> 00:01:03.422
For what?

13
00:01:03.456 --> 00:01:05.224
For the death of
my mother. so you could

14
00:01:05.258 --> 00:01:09.127
install this whore.

15
00:01:09.162 --> 00:01:12.064
And for banishing me
so I'd be silenced.

16
00:01:12.098 --> 00:01:13.432
I sent you
away for an education.

17
00:01:13.466 --> 00:01:15.067
Fifteen years in
a nunnery. I learned more

18
00:01:15.101 --> 00:01:18.003
than you can imagine.

19
00:01:18.037 --> 00:01:22.808
Father. I'm
your only child.

20
00:01:22.842 --> 00:01:28.213
Why wouldn't you
welcome me home?

21
00:01:28.248 --> 00:01:30.115
You've lived too
long without my guidance.

22
00:01:30.149 --> 00:01:31.950
This isn't your home now.

23
00:01:31.985 --> 00:01:34.653
And I no longer
have a daughter.

24
00:01:34.687 --> 00:01:37.456
Don't turn your
back on me. Father!

25
00:01:37.490 --> 00:01:39.491
You're not
welcome Morgan.

26
00:01:39.526 --> 00:01:41.226
Goodbye.

27
00:01:41.261 --> 00:01:43.729
Igraine. leave
her.

28
00:03:38.778 --> 00:03:42.147
Uther! Uther!

29
00:03:44.217 --> 00:03:47.152
Uther? Uther!
What's wrong?

30
00:03:47.186 --> 00:03:52.090
Help! Somebody help
him! Uther!

31
00:03:53.559 --> 00:03:55.227
Help us!

32
00:03:59.766 --> 00:04:00.999
Out of my way!

33
00:04:01.034 --> 00:04:02.901
Open the gates!

34
00:04:16.516 --> 00:04:18.850
Help him! Help him!

35
00:04:18.885 --> 00:04:21.086
Take the
King to his chambers! Now!

36
00:04:22.221 --> 00:04:26.725
Alleluia dilexi quoniam exaudiet

37
00:04:26.759 --> 00:04:30.429
Dominus vocem orationis
meae Quia inclinavit aurem

38
00:04:30.463 --> 00:04:34.733
Whatever powers
you have. use them now!

39
00:04:47.680 --> 00:04:52.818
Uther.
you're going to die.

40
00:04:52.852 --> 00:04:56.922
The poison was too strong.

41
00:04:57.924 --> 00:05:01.727
Put your hand to this.

42
00:05:01.761 --> 00:05:04.863
For Briton and the boy.

43
00:05:29.322 --> 00:05:32.791
His time is done.

44
00:05:36.162 --> 00:05:38.430
Merlin!

45
00:06:03.989 --> 00:06:07.989
<font color=#00ff00>♪ Camelot 1x01 ♪</font>
<font color=#00ffff>Homecoming</font>
Original Air Date on February 25. 2011

46
00:06:07.990 --> 00:06:11.990
== sync. corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> ==

47
00:07:46.559 --> 00:07:53.265
In principio-erat-verbum.

48
00:07:53.299 --> 00:07:55.533
In the beginning
was the Word.

49
00:07:55.568 --> 00:07:58.203
And the Word was--

50
00:07:58.237 --> 00:08:01.673
God. yes.

51
00:08:01.707 --> 00:08:03.275
This isn't Latin study.

52
00:08:03.309 --> 00:08:06.912
No. but it is
definitely worship.

53
00:08:09.515 --> 00:08:11.483
<i>Arthur!</i>

54
00:08:11.517 --> 00:08:14.252
It can't be!

55
00:08:17.723 --> 00:08:19.057
Hey!

56
00:08:19.091 --> 00:08:20.258
You bastard!

57
00:08:20.293 --> 00:08:22.694
Kay. listen-she
said you two were over!

58
00:08:22.728 --> 00:08:23.995
No. I did not.

59
00:08:24.030 --> 00:08:26.031
Thanks a lot.

60
00:08:29.535 --> 00:08:32.404
Stop it! Both of you!

61
00:08:33.839 --> 00:08:37.809
Ah!

62
00:08:39.845 --> 00:08:41.546
I should kill you.

63
00:08:41.580 --> 00:08:44.649
How did
you even find us?

64
00:08:44.684 --> 00:08:47.319
I know where you
bring your girls.

65
00:08:47.353 --> 00:08:49.821
And now mine. too.

66
00:08:52.124 --> 00:08:56.761
Get dressed. I was sent to
find you. There's a visitor.

67
00:08:56.796 --> 00:08:59.898
What's that
got to do with me?

68
00:09:10.476 --> 00:09:11.943
It's bad. I know.

69
00:09:11.978 --> 00:09:13.078
I shouldn't have done it.
I wasn't thinking.

70
00:09:13.112 --> 00:09:14.245
No. you
were thinking.

71
00:09:14.280 --> 00:09:15.246
You were thinking.
if I get caught.

72
00:09:15.281 --> 00:09:16.514
I can talk my way
out of this.

73
00:09:16.549 --> 00:09:18.750
It was a mistake.
We got carried away-

74
00:09:18.784 --> 00:09:19.751
twice.

75
00:09:19.785 --> 00:09:21.553
Shut up. Please.
just shut up.

76
00:09:21.587 --> 00:09:23.555
Sometimes
these things happen.

77
00:09:23.589 --> 00:09:25.557
It's like she's Cleopatra.
you're Caesar.

78
00:09:25.591 --> 00:09:26.725
and I'm Mark Antony.

79
00:09:26.759 --> 00:09:28.460
No. You're
really not-at all.

80
00:09:28.494 --> 00:09:29.928
We can't let a
woman come between us.

81
00:09:29.962 --> 00:09:31.062
Can we. brother?

82
00:09:31.097 --> 00:09:34.399
Everything
comes easy for you.

83
00:09:34.433 --> 00:09:38.336
And you don't
appreciate it.

84
00:09:44.343 --> 00:09:46.311
What's going on?

85
00:09:46.345 --> 00:09:50.081
Mother?

86
00:09:50.116 --> 00:09:52.350
Father?

87
00:09:54.887 --> 00:09:57.722
He's here.

88
00:10:07.299 --> 00:10:10.535
So you're the boy.

89
00:10:10.569 --> 00:10:11.736
I'm Arthur.
Who are you?

90
00:10:11.771 --> 00:10:12.937
His name is Merlin-

91
00:10:12.972 --> 00:10:14.239
and he's not
welcome here!

92
00:10:14.273 --> 00:10:15.907
Then he'll
be on his way!

93
00:10:15.941 --> 00:10:17.142
Put down your sword. Kay.
No!

94
00:10:17.176 --> 00:10:18.510
Do as
you're told. boy!

95
00:10:18.544 --> 00:10:20.445
Will someone
explain what is happening here?

96
00:10:22.615 --> 00:10:25.450
The King is dead.
Murdered.

97
00:10:25.484 --> 00:10:26.818
So?

98
00:10:26.852 --> 00:10:29.354
Uther died
with no legitimate son.

99
00:10:32.825 --> 00:10:34.859
What's that
got to do with us?

100
00:10:34.894 --> 00:10:37.962
Not them.
You-are Uther's son.

101
00:10:46.072 --> 00:10:48.106
No.

102
00:10:48.140 --> 00:10:52.010
My parents are standing here.

103
00:10:52.044 --> 00:10:56.448
Tell him. Tell him.

104
00:11:01.320 --> 00:11:04.589
He's telling
the truth. Arthur.

105
00:11:04.623 --> 00:11:08.359
He can't be.
How can he be?

106
00:11:08.394 --> 00:11:11.262
Merlin brought
you to us when you were

107
00:11:11.297 --> 00:11:13.765
less than a week old.

108
00:11:13.799 --> 00:11:16.434
We swore to
look after you.

109
00:11:16.469 --> 00:11:18.503
What?

110
00:11:18.537 --> 00:11:21.439
The King is dead.

111
00:11:21.474 --> 00:11:26.578
Long live the King.

112
00:11:28.681 --> 00:11:30.148
Take your
lies and get out!

113
00:11:30.182 --> 00:11:34.686
Arthur. Arthur.
give me the blade.

114
00:11:34.720 --> 00:11:36.821
Give me the blade.

115
00:11:38.691 --> 00:11:42.026
You tell
him how this happened.

116
00:11:42.061 --> 00:11:44.529
You tell him the
story of his birth.

117
00:11:44.563 --> 00:11:46.664
The details
aren't important.

118
00:11:46.699 --> 00:11:50.101
They are to him!

119
00:11:50.136 --> 00:11:52.704
Arthur. I
should've told you before.

120
00:11:52.738 --> 00:11:57.909
I'm-I'm so sorry. son.

121
00:11:57.943 --> 00:12:00.578
Rest tonight.

122
00:12:00.613 --> 00:12:03.381
Tomorrow. we leave.

123
00:12:06.685 --> 00:12:08.153
Where is she?

124
00:12:08.187 --> 00:12:11.456
Lady Igraine remains
in mourning in her chamber.

125
00:12:11.490 --> 00:12:12.991
And the men?

126
00:12:13.025 --> 00:12:14.425
Most are gone.

127
00:12:14.460 --> 00:12:15.460
On whose authority?

128
00:12:15.494 --> 00:12:16.694
Merlin's.

129
00:12:16.729 --> 00:12:18.730
The night after your
father's death his

130
00:12:18.764 --> 00:12:21.032
warriors packed up their
belongings and left.

131
00:12:22.268 --> 00:12:24.269
Then we'll
move on our own.

132
00:12:24.303 --> 00:12:26.137
Better and stronger.

133
00:12:26.172 --> 00:12:27.472
We?

134
00:12:27.506 --> 00:12:30.642
You answer to me now.

135
00:13:02.575 --> 00:13:06.277
Thank you.

136
00:13:18.257 --> 00:13:20.225
Pull down those banners!

137
00:13:20.259 --> 00:13:23.828
Confiscate all the weapons
and someone find the kitchens!

138
00:13:23.862 --> 00:13:26.030
I'm bloody starving.

139
00:13:26.065 --> 00:13:27.765
The doors are
open to you. my Lord.

140
00:13:27.800 --> 00:13:30.335
There's no need for force.

141
00:13:30.369 --> 00:13:32.270
Are you the
one who summoned me?

142
00:13:32.304 --> 00:13:34.505
I'm Uther's
daughter and sole heir:

143
00:13:34.540 --> 00:13:36.241
Morgan Pendragon.

144
00:13:36.275 --> 00:13:37.709
Even as we
speak. my men are

145
00:13:37.743 --> 00:13:41.145
slaughtering all those
still loyal to Uther.

146
00:13:41.180 --> 00:13:43.481
Why would you
call me here?

147
00:13:43.515 --> 00:13:45.283
To offer an alliance.

148
00:13:45.317 --> 00:13:46.284
Who with?

149
00:13:46.318 --> 00:13:47.285
Me.

150
00:13:50.322 --> 00:13:52.056
You?

151
00:13:52.091 --> 00:13:54.993
Who better than
you. King Lot. my father's

152
00:13:55.027 --> 00:13:58.129
strongest opponent.

153
00:13:58.163 --> 00:14:00.198
I am
immune to flattery.

154
00:14:00.232 --> 00:14:02.066
And yet you came
when asked.

155
00:14:02.101 --> 00:14:03.901
You've nothing
to offer me.

156
00:14:03.936 --> 00:14:06.504
I hold this castle.

157
00:14:06.538 --> 00:14:10.241
I could split
you from your gut to your

158
00:14:10.276 --> 00:14:13.177
throat and still take it.

159
00:14:13.212 --> 00:14:14.445
You're cleverer than that.

160
00:14:14.480 --> 00:14:15.780
Am I?

161
00:14:15.814 --> 00:14:17.582
Kill me and you're
just another warlord

162
00:14:17.616 --> 00:14:19.484
taking yet another castle.

163
00:14:19.518 --> 00:14:20.485
But if we stand together-

164
00:14:20.519 --> 00:14:21.753
I stand alone.

165
00:14:21.787 --> 00:14:23.488
If we forge a
union. we'd have the

166
00:14:23.522 --> 00:14:26.891
strength to
unite the realm.

167
00:14:26.925 --> 00:14:30.261
As King and Queen.

168
00:14:31.864 --> 00:14:34.532
There is already
a Queen within these walls.

169
00:14:34.566 --> 00:14:38.169
I could take her and still
sit on Uther's throne.

170
00:14:38.203 --> 00:14:39.370
She's to be exiled.

171
00:14:39.405 --> 00:14:41.873
Oh. is she now?

172
00:14:41.907 --> 00:14:43.408
Yes.

173
00:14:43.442 --> 00:14:46.844
You're very
confident in your plans.

174
00:14:46.879 --> 00:14:50.181
I am.

175
00:14:50.215 --> 00:14:55.520
What makes
you so special?

176
00:15:03.395 --> 00:15:07.532
Come near
me. I'll kill you.

177
00:15:10.936 --> 00:15:14.238
Don't issue
empty threats.

178
00:15:14.273 --> 00:15:18.543
Who are you?

179
00:15:19.745 --> 00:15:23.414
I knew
Uther Pendragon.

180
00:15:23.449 --> 00:15:28.386
I was at his side
when he died.

181
00:15:33.759 --> 00:15:38.963
The King's will. signed by his
own hand. bearing his seal.

182
00:15:38.997 --> 00:15:42.500
attesting to your birth.

183
00:15:42.534 --> 00:15:46.804
This was your father's.

184
00:15:46.839 --> 00:15:49.941
Take it.

185
00:15:49.975 --> 00:15:55.680
When you were born. I took
you and brought you here.

186
00:15:55.714 --> 00:15:58.950
You may be of King's blood
but Uther was a barbarian.

187
00:15:58.984 --> 00:16:03.588
acing you here made
you so much more.

188
00:16:03.622 --> 00:16:07.358
I told Ector how to
raise and educate you.

189
00:16:07.393 --> 00:16:09.961
He swore to always
keep you safe.

190
00:16:09.995 --> 00:16:14.665
They raised you well.

191
00:16:18.971 --> 00:16:22.473
Perhaps too well.

192
00:16:24.843 --> 00:16:30.381
Why? Why do
you need me?

193
00:16:33.285 --> 00:16:36.120
Everything in time.

194
00:16:42.928 --> 00:16:46.297
I sometimes wondered
why they doted more on you.

195
00:16:46.331 --> 00:16:48.499
How come you always
got away with so much.

196
00:16:48.534 --> 00:16:49.500
It was
never like that.

197
00:16:49.535 --> 00:16:50.935
It's always
been like that.

198
00:16:50.969 --> 00:16:53.671
You've just never seen it.

199
00:16:53.705 --> 00:16:55.606
You're used to the world
falling at your feet the

200
00:16:55.641 --> 00:16:57.909
moment you smile.

201
00:16:57.943 --> 00:16:59.343
But it's all right.

202
00:16:59.378 --> 00:17:00.511
This makes sense of it.

203
00:17:00.546 --> 00:17:03.681
They treated you like
you were special.

204
00:17:03.715 --> 00:17:05.183
Because you are.

205
00:17:05.217 --> 00:17:06.350
At last you
finally admit it.

206
00:17:14.159 --> 00:17:15.827
Hey. this doesn't
change anything.

207
00:17:15.861 --> 00:17:18.029
You're still my brother.

208
00:17:18.063 --> 00:17:21.866
And you're still infuriating.

209
00:17:21.900 --> 00:17:25.970
What do I do? I can't
just leave! This is my home.

210
00:17:26.004 --> 00:17:27.205
This is what I know. Here.

211
00:17:27.239 --> 00:17:29.674
But what you're
being offered is better.

212
00:17:29.708 --> 00:17:31.542
Going to battle.
leading the land.

213
00:17:31.577 --> 00:17:32.844
It's what every
man dreams of.

214
00:17:32.878 --> 00:17:35.480
No. it's
what you dream of.

215
00:17:35.514 --> 00:17:37.982
The rest of us
dream about girls.

216
00:17:38.016 --> 00:17:42.954
You think a leader
won't get his choice of girls?

217
00:17:42.988 --> 00:17:47.625
Why shouldn't it
be your destiny?

218
00:17:49.461 --> 00:17:55.166
If it was me. I'd
go-in an instant.

219
00:18:39.745 --> 00:18:43.381
So. you're coming.

220
00:18:43.415 --> 00:18:44.882
I'm not
saying I believe you.

221
00:18:44.917 --> 00:18:46.884
It's just I want to
see it for myself.

222
00:18:48.387 --> 00:18:51.289
You're ready.

223
00:18:52.424 --> 00:18:54.525
Why didn't
you tell me?

224
00:18:54.560 --> 00:18:57.194
I was
afraid of losing you.

225
00:18:57.229 --> 00:18:59.063
Because you are my son.

226
00:18:59.097 --> 00:19:03.134
You'll always be my mother.

227
00:19:05.470 --> 00:19:07.505
I place
him in your care.

228
00:19:07.539 --> 00:19:08.573
You keep him safe.

229
00:19:08.607 --> 00:19:10.708
You have my word.

230
00:19:16.381 --> 00:19:18.516
It's what
you were born for.

231
00:19:18.550 --> 00:19:20.585
It's what we've
guided you for.

232
00:19:20.619 --> 00:19:22.620
You remember what
I taught you.

233
00:19:22.654 --> 00:19:26.057
When you make decisions.
you use this in

234
00:19:26.091 --> 00:19:28.092
conjunction with this.

235
00:19:28.126 --> 00:19:29.961
And you never use this!

236
00:19:29.995 --> 00:19:34.799
I'll try and remember that.

237
00:19:34.833 --> 00:19:39.103
No son ever had a better
father. I-I want you to know-

238
00:19:39.137 --> 00:19:41.172
I know. I know. I know.

239
00:19:43.208 --> 00:19:46.644
I love you.

240
00:19:50.415 --> 00:19:53.217
You've given me
everything my entire life

241
00:19:53.251 --> 00:19:56.020
and I feel guilty asking
for anything more.

242
00:19:56.054 --> 00:19:59.991
But-I need Kay.

243
00:20:00.025 --> 00:20:01.025
I want him with me.

244
00:20:01.059 --> 00:20:03.594
Yes. yes!

245
00:20:03.629 --> 00:20:05.529
Whatever this is.
I can't do it without you.

246
00:20:05.564 --> 00:20:07.164
We were
scared you'd never ask.

247
00:20:08.634 --> 00:20:12.436
Together. you're stronger.

248
00:20:12.471 --> 00:20:13.871
It's time.

249
00:20:45.237 --> 00:20:46.370
Say my name!

250
00:20:46.405 --> 00:20:48.139
Morgan!

251
00:20:48.173 --> 00:20:49.373
Who will I be?

252
00:20:49.408 --> 00:20:50.708
Queen of the realm!

253
00:20:50.742 --> 00:20:52.576
Are you
fit to be my King?

254
00:20:52.611 --> 00:20:55.413
You know I am!

255
00:20:55.447 --> 00:20:57.114
What will you give me?

256
00:20:57.149 --> 00:21:00.084
Undying loyalty!

257
00:21:00.118 --> 00:21:01.385
Swear your fealty!

258
00:21:01.420 --> 00:21:02.820
Swear yours to me!

259
00:21:02.854 --> 00:21:04.088
SWEAR IT!

260
00:21:04.122 --> 00:21:05.456
I swear!

261
00:21:05.490 --> 00:21:06.757
On what-

262
00:21:06.792 --> 00:21:08.726
- My oath-
- Yes!

263
00:21:08.760 --> 00:21:09.727
My life!

264
00:21:09.761 --> 00:21:10.728
Yes!

265
00:21:10.762 --> 00:21:12.563
And your blood!

266
00:21:12.597 --> 00:21:15.299
My blood!

267
00:21:22.174 --> 00:21:27.678
Where did
you learn that. huh?

268
00:21:27.713 --> 00:21:32.483
Your father dies. and you
banish your own mother

269
00:21:32.517 --> 00:21:33.951
from her home. Impressive.

270
00:21:33.985 --> 00:21:36.954
Stepmother.

271
00:21:36.988 --> 00:21:38.756
I'm the only one
of Uther's blood.

272
00:21:38.790 --> 00:21:42.193
His castle and realm
should be mine.

273
00:21:42.227 --> 00:21:47.732
So you summon
me. Uther's worst enemy.

274
00:21:47.766 --> 00:21:52.970
You propose an alliance
and then seduce me. even

275
00:21:53.004 --> 00:21:56.440
as your father's
body cools.

276
00:21:56.475 --> 00:22:00.745
Is there no end
to your ambition?

277
00:22:00.779 --> 00:22:02.480
Are you complaining?

278
00:22:02.514 --> 00:22:04.281
No.

279
00:22:04.316 --> 00:22:06.784
Just curious.

280
00:22:06.818 --> 00:22:09.086
A queen still
requires a king.

281
00:22:09.121 --> 00:22:10.488
Yes.

282
00:22:10.522 --> 00:22:12.723
Together.
we'll unite the realm.

283
00:22:12.758 --> 00:22:14.325
Yes.

284
00:22:16.495 --> 00:22:20.564
I'll set her
on the way myself.

285
00:22:20.599 --> 00:22:22.366
Yes.

286
00:22:35.280 --> 00:22:37.982
It suits
you up there.

287
00:22:38.016 --> 00:22:39.617
Where will you go?

288
00:22:39.651 --> 00:22:40.818
Your father had
plenty of allies who'll

289
00:22:40.852 --> 00:22:42.987
give me space.

290
00:22:43.021 --> 00:22:45.923
Was there anything else. or
did you just come to gloat?

291
00:22:45.957 --> 00:22:49.426
Just give thanks
you're leaving here alive.

292
00:22:49.461 --> 00:22:52.329
I did
nothing to harm you.

293
00:22:52.364 --> 00:22:55.266
Indeed. my
Lady. you did nothing.

294
00:22:55.300 --> 00:22:56.867
You did nothing when my
mother was murdered.

295
00:22:56.902 --> 00:22:58.769
so that you could
take her place.

296
00:22:58.804 --> 00:23:01.939
And you did nothing when
my father banished me.

297
00:23:01.973 --> 00:23:04.341
No queen
questions her king!

298
00:23:04.376 --> 00:23:05.843
And I thought my
opinion of you couldn't

299
00:23:05.877 --> 00:23:09.213
get any lower.

300
00:23:11.616 --> 00:23:14.985
Safe travels!

301
00:23:16.254 --> 00:23:18.622
The land is treacherous.

302
00:23:20.258 --> 00:23:21.492
I bring a
message from Merlin.

303
00:23:21.526 --> 00:23:23.661
Merlin? What
does he want?

304
00:23:23.695 --> 00:23:25.763
He asks you
attend Uther's son at the

305
00:23:25.797 --> 00:23:29.066
ancient castle of Camelot.

306
00:23:29.100 --> 00:23:30.634
Uther's son?

307
00:23:30.669 --> 00:23:33.003
That's what
I was told to deliver.

308
00:23:34.806 --> 00:23:39.510
He has a son.

309
00:23:39.544 --> 00:23:43.080
I have the only
true claim to the throne.

310
00:23:43.114 --> 00:23:44.748
This is Merlin's game.

311
00:23:44.783 --> 00:23:47.151
So. we'll play with him.

312
00:24:16.915 --> 00:24:18.582
If you were
responsible for my birth.

313
00:24:18.617 --> 00:24:21.986
I deserve to know more
about who you are.

314
00:24:22.020 --> 00:24:25.589
Stop asking about
me and think about who you are.

315
00:24:25.624 --> 00:24:30.728
Are you
really a sorcerer?

316
00:24:30.762 --> 00:24:34.999
I can do things
others believe impossible.

317
00:24:35.033 --> 00:24:38.135
Is that sorcery?

318
00:24:38.169 --> 00:24:44.141
Go on then. Show me.
Prove it to me.

319
00:24:45.744 --> 00:24:47.978
You pull me from one coast
to the other and you tell

320
00:24:48.013 --> 00:24:52.549
me nothing!

321
00:24:58.390 --> 00:25:01.959
You asked
me why I need you.

322
00:25:03.495 --> 00:25:07.064
I had a vision
of what was to come.

323
00:25:07.098 --> 00:25:09.266
What sort of vision?

324
00:25:10.368 --> 00:25:11.535
The darkness of man.

325
00:25:11.569 --> 00:25:13.604
I won't let it
happen again.

326
00:25:13.638 --> 00:25:14.638
Are you saying you
had this vision before I

327
00:25:14.673 --> 00:25:18.342
was conceived?

328
00:25:19.444 --> 00:25:22.079
The past doesn't matter.

329
00:25:22.113 --> 00:25:25.015
Define yourself in the
present and you might rule

330
00:25:25.050 --> 00:25:26.951
in the future.

331
00:25:45.870 --> 00:25:49.506
Dear God.

332
00:25:50.809 --> 00:25:52.276
It's already begun.

333
00:25:52.310 --> 00:25:53.610
What?

334
00:25:53.645 --> 00:25:55.379
With no King in
place. there'll be carnage

335
00:25:55.413 --> 00:25:59.216
across the land.

336
00:26:00.452 --> 00:26:03.187
What're you doing?

337
00:26:03.221 --> 00:26:04.254
Whoever these men
are. they deserve a

338
00:26:04.289 --> 00:26:05.789
Christian burial.

339
00:26:05.824 --> 00:26:07.958
They're
long past saving.

340
00:26:07.993 --> 00:26:10.828
Arthur-tell him.

341
00:26:10.862 --> 00:26:12.629
We stay here. we're
a target for whoever did this.

342
00:26:12.664 --> 00:26:18.469
Stop worrying about the
dead-the living need us more!

343
00:26:18.503 --> 00:26:21.105
Merlin's right.
We have to get out of here.

344
00:26:21.139 --> 00:26:23.374
We can't help them now.

345
00:26:25.076 --> 00:26:26.510
Yah!

346
00:26:26.544 --> 00:26:28.178
Let's move.

347
00:26:39.324 --> 00:26:41.258
We rest here.

348
00:26:41.292 --> 00:26:43.894
This village?
Is that wise?

349
00:26:43.928 --> 00:26:45.596
We'll find out.

350
00:26:55.173 --> 00:27:00.544
Fear spreads like plague.

351
00:27:12.357 --> 00:27:14.658
Stay on your
horses and ride on through.

352
00:27:14.692 --> 00:27:16.760
We are on
our way to the coast.

353
00:27:16.795 --> 00:27:18.762
We were hoping for
shelter tonight.

354
00:27:18.797 --> 00:27:24.435
There's no
welcome here.

355
00:27:24.469 --> 00:27:27.037
Not even
for an old friend?

356
00:27:27.072 --> 00:27:30.574
Merlin! Is that you?

357
00:27:30.608 --> 00:27:32.142
That's more like it.

358
00:27:32.177 --> 00:27:33.577
It's been too long.

359
00:27:38.383 --> 00:27:39.750
It's people like
these that will be next to

360
00:27:39.784 --> 00:27:44.888
the slaughter if you don't
fulfill your destiny.

361
00:27:44.923 --> 00:27:46.457
What would you have
done if I hadn't come with you.

362
00:27:46.491 --> 00:27:49.693
A stranger says
you're the future king.

363
00:27:49.727 --> 00:27:53.063
Maybe it takes a night.
maybe it takes a year.

364
00:27:53.098 --> 00:27:56.033
but in the end you're too
curious not to come.

365
00:27:56.067 --> 00:27:57.434
You think you
know me that well?

366
00:27:57.469 --> 00:28:02.072
I watched you
since you were a child.

367
00:28:02.107 --> 00:28:04.875
Tell me about my birth.

368
00:28:08.780 --> 00:28:13.951
Your father.
Uther. desired a woman

369
00:28:13.985 --> 00:28:18.155
named Igraine. who belonged
to a rival warlord.

370
00:28:18.189 --> 00:28:21.291
the Duke of Cornwall.

371
00:28:21.326 --> 00:28:25.329
Unable to best his forces.

372
00:28:25.363 --> 00:28:29.500
Uther changed tactics

373
00:28:29.534 --> 00:28:31.535
and summoned me.

374
00:28:31.569 --> 00:28:34.037
To do what?

375
00:28:34.072 --> 00:28:36.273
To change Uther to
resemble Cornwall so he

376
00:28:36.307 --> 00:28:38.842
could have Igraine
for just one night.

377
00:28:45.150 --> 00:28:46.750
You want me to
believe I'm the product of

378
00:28:46.784 --> 00:28:48.485
sorcery and rape?

379
00:28:48.520 --> 00:28:50.821
You were
conceived that night.

380
00:28:56.161 --> 00:28:57.961
Merlin. I want the truth.

381
00:28:57.996 --> 00:29:00.697
Not some story to make
me believe in magic.

382
00:29:00.732 --> 00:29:02.199
I don't care
what you believe.

383
00:29:02.233 --> 00:29:04.568
But I've sworn off those
vows a long time ago.

384
00:29:04.602 --> 00:29:05.903
Why?

385
00:29:05.937 --> 00:29:08.005
- Because they cost.
- Cost how?

386
00:29:08.039 --> 00:29:10.641
You want me
to finish or not?

387
00:29:13.044 --> 00:29:15.479
So Uther
gave me to you.

388
00:29:15.513 --> 00:29:20.484
You were my payment.

389
00:29:25.023 --> 00:29:26.657
Why would you
take a child as payment?

390
00:29:26.691 --> 00:29:29.226
This realm needs a
leader better than any who

391
00:29:29.260 --> 00:29:31.395
has come before.

392
00:29:31.429 --> 00:29:34.598
With Uther's blood line
and Ector's guidance.

393
00:29:34.632 --> 00:29:36.800
that can be you.

394
00:29:36.834 --> 00:29:39.336
I know you've got
questions. but I will be

395
00:29:39.370 --> 00:29:44.741
at your side and we will
find the answers together.

396
00:29:44.776 --> 00:29:47.044
We are going to build a
land full of hope and

397
00:29:47.078 --> 00:29:51.848
honor where fear is
extinguished. to which

398
00:29:51.883 --> 00:29:57.287
people will flock from far
and wide. seeking out our

399
00:29:57.322 --> 00:30:00.090
beacon of light.

400
00:30:00.124 --> 00:30:06.029
Tomorrow we ride to an
ancient seat of power.

401
00:30:06.064 --> 00:30:12.202
You can be the greatest of men
in the greatest of lands.

402
00:30:13.204 --> 00:30:17.040
Trust me. Arthur.

403
00:30:48.673 --> 00:30:50.540
Arthur!

404
00:31:16.868 --> 00:31:18.869
An outrider for King Lot.

405
00:31:18.903 --> 00:31:20.370
These are Lot's colors.

406
00:31:20.405 --> 00:31:23.473
You're not even installed
and you're starting a war!

407
00:31:23.508 --> 00:31:25.709
Back on the horses!

408
00:31:25.743 --> 00:31:28.445
If we're here when they
find him. you won't live

409
00:31:28.479 --> 00:31:30.514
to be King.

410
00:31:56.541 --> 00:31:59.476
Camelot. Yah!

411
00:32:41.853 --> 00:32:43.820
It's a ruin.

412
00:32:43.855 --> 00:32:47.557
The Romans built it.

413
00:32:47.592 --> 00:32:52.329
We'll create
the future here.

414
00:32:52.363 --> 00:32:54.064
This has good
position. strong

415
00:32:54.098 --> 00:32:55.599
fortifications.

416
00:32:55.633 --> 00:32:57.100
And no one will expect it.

417
00:32:57.135 --> 00:32:58.535
This is not what
I thought you meant!

418
00:32:58.569 --> 00:32:59.569
I thought there'd be armies.
and weapons and servants!

419
00:32:59.604 --> 00:33:00.904
And girls.

420
00:33:00.938 --> 00:33:01.972
There has to be
more than this. right?

421
00:33:02.006 --> 00:33:03.607
I mean. I must have money.

422
00:33:03.641 --> 00:33:04.975
No.

423
00:33:05.009 --> 00:33:06.209
Why didn't you
say that before we left!

424
00:33:06.244 --> 00:33:08.078
You wouldn't have come.

425
00:33:08.112 --> 00:33:09.079
You didn't say
it would be like this.

426
00:33:09.113 --> 00:33:10.747
You didn't ask.

427
00:33:10.782 --> 00:33:12.716
We're in a fight for our
lives. for the soul of

428
00:33:12.750 --> 00:33:14.718
this country.

429
00:33:14.752 --> 00:33:18.622
Now. there are
people waiting.

430
00:33:28.366 --> 00:33:31.701
The Great
Hall of Camelot.

431
00:33:43.815 --> 00:33:45.315
Meet those
who have sworn their

432
00:33:45.349 --> 00:33:49.119
allegiance to you.

433
00:33:53.691 --> 00:33:59.663
Ulfius! Leontes!
Brastias! Pelinor!

434
00:34:03.868 --> 00:34:05.769
Your father
was a great leader.

435
00:34:05.803 --> 00:34:07.571
Our loyalty passes to you.

436
00:34:07.605 --> 00:34:09.072
We stand at your bidding.
ready to defend the

437
00:34:09.106 --> 00:34:14.010
Pendragon line.

438
00:34:17.048 --> 00:34:20.383
I never
knew Uther.

439
00:34:20.418 --> 00:34:23.587
But if he inspired such
loyalty. I am humbled to

440
00:34:23.621 --> 00:34:27.557
stand before you and I'll
do whatever I can to

441
00:34:27.592 --> 00:34:30.927
justify your allegiance.

442
00:34:30.962 --> 00:34:33.897
We are your servants.

443
00:34:37.301 --> 00:34:40.504
These are your allies.

444
00:34:40.538 --> 00:34:42.539
Your enemies are much
greater in number.

445
00:34:42.573 --> 00:34:44.341
Something else you
forgot to mention earlier.

446
00:34:44.375 --> 00:34:47.677
King Lot of
Lothian and Orkney.

447
00:34:47.712 --> 00:34:54.017
The new Duke of Cornwall; Kings
Nentes. Scotland. and Carados.

448
00:34:54.051 --> 00:34:55.218
I've summoned them here.

449
00:34:55.253 --> 00:34:56.486
You've done what?

450
00:34:56.521 --> 00:34:58.555
So they all can
recognize you as the true

451
00:34:58.589 --> 00:35:01.925
heir of Uther Pendragon.

452
00:35:01.959 --> 00:35:04.194
What if they don't?

453
00:35:04.228 --> 00:35:06.263
They must.

454
00:35:10.501 --> 00:35:12.569
These are your chambers.

455
00:35:12.603 --> 00:35:17.173
I had your father's
effects brought here.

456
00:35:25.449 --> 00:35:28.852
What was he
like? My father.

457
00:35:33.758 --> 00:35:37.327
Unyielding.

458
00:35:37.361 --> 00:35:39.996
That's it?

459
00:35:40.031 --> 00:35:42.432
The life of a man and
you take one word.

460
00:35:42.466 --> 00:35:43.567
It's all
you need to know.

461
00:35:43.601 --> 00:35:44.901
No. it's not!

462
00:35:44.936 --> 00:35:46.636
I want to know everything.

463
00:35:46.671 --> 00:35:49.873
What he ate. what he
drank. how he stood.

464
00:35:49.907 --> 00:35:52.909
Who he loved. what made
him laugh or weep.

465
00:35:52.944 --> 00:35:54.144
And you give me one word.

466
00:35:54.178 --> 00:35:55.946
Anyone else can
tell you his character

467
00:35:55.980 --> 00:35:57.614
and contradictions.

468
00:35:57.648 --> 00:35:59.883
I gave you the word
you most require.

469
00:35:59.917 --> 00:36:03.086
The aspect you
must take from him.

470
00:36:03.120 --> 00:36:06.556
An unyielding strength.

471
00:36:06.591 --> 00:36:08.992
Because from now on.
everyone will challenge

472
00:36:09.026 --> 00:36:13.296
you. on everything.

473
00:36:13.331 --> 00:36:15.832
You need to be certain.

474
00:36:15.866 --> 00:36:18.301
What if I'm not?

475
00:36:18.336 --> 00:36:20.804
You have to be.

476
00:36:20.838 --> 00:36:21.871
What if I'm wrong?

477
00:36:21.906 --> 00:36:24.341
You can't be.

478
00:36:24.375 --> 00:36:25.942
Oh. one more thing.

479
00:36:25.977 --> 00:36:30.447
Uther also had a daughter.
Your half-sister.

480
00:36:34.218 --> 00:36:36.519
He installs
a child in a ruin.

481
00:36:36.554 --> 00:36:38.855
and expects the
kingdom to kneel?

482
00:36:38.889 --> 00:36:41.524
I think the sorcerer's
mind is addled.

483
00:36:41.559 --> 00:36:42.792
No. he's clever.

484
00:36:42.827 --> 00:36:44.494
This was a power. once.

485
00:36:44.528 --> 00:36:47.764
He believes he
can awaken it.

486
00:36:47.798 --> 00:36:49.833
Are you all right?

487
00:36:49.867 --> 00:36:54.471
The games
of men exhaust me.

488
00:36:54.505 --> 00:36:56.306
We ride in strong.

489
00:36:56.340 --> 00:36:59.042
If this pretender
wears my father's robes.

490
00:36:59.076 --> 00:37:00.777
I shall gouge his eyes.

491
00:37:02.313 --> 00:37:03.446
On!

492
00:37:23.334 --> 00:37:24.934
That's your sister?

493
00:37:57.101 --> 00:37:58.535
No.

494
00:37:58.569 --> 00:38:01.371
He's Uther's son.
I have proof.

495
00:38:01.405 --> 00:38:03.840
My father had
no legitimate son.

496
00:38:03.874 --> 00:38:05.341
I would have known.

497
00:38:05.376 --> 00:38:06.976
Honestly. this is as
strange to me as it is to you.

498
00:38:07.011 --> 00:38:07.977
But when Merlin-

499
00:38:08.012 --> 00:38:10.780
It talks. too.

500
00:38:10.815 --> 00:38:13.416
It's pretty. it talks.

501
00:38:13.451 --> 00:38:15.351
But it is not an heir.

502
00:38:15.386 --> 00:38:17.620
We can work together
to honor our father-

503
00:38:17.655 --> 00:38:21.691
You didn't know my father.

504
00:38:21.726 --> 00:38:25.762
Look at it. Not even a
convincing pretender.

505
00:38:25.796 --> 00:38:30.033
You're not made of kings.
boy. but of common clay.

506
00:38:30.067 --> 00:38:32.902
How much did the
sorcerer promise you?

507
00:38:32.937 --> 00:38:35.638
He didn't
promise me anything.

508
00:38:39.744 --> 00:38:41.578
Why are you
doing this to me?

509
00:38:41.612 --> 00:38:43.847
This isn't personal.

510
00:38:43.881 --> 00:38:46.216
This is for the country.

511
00:38:46.250 --> 00:38:48.017
This is my birthright.

512
00:38:48.052 --> 00:38:53.056
Is it? We should ask
his mother. Queen Igraine.

513
00:39:01.766 --> 00:39:02.999
You were childless.

514
00:39:03.033 --> 00:39:04.834
I never spoke of this.

515
00:39:04.869 --> 00:39:07.070
This is some
other man's bastard.

516
00:39:07.104 --> 00:39:12.809
Not my father's. I
would have known.

517
00:39:12.843 --> 00:39:18.581
And yet you didn't.

518
00:39:28.559 --> 00:39:33.229
Is this the boy I took
from you when he was born?

519
00:39:33.264 --> 00:39:38.234
Yes. I believe he is.

520
00:39:38.269 --> 00:39:42.839
This is Uther's son. My son.

521
00:39:48.379 --> 00:39:52.816
No. Fuck this.

522
00:39:52.850 --> 00:39:56.252
You think
this is the end of it?

523
00:40:01.826 --> 00:40:03.793
Merlin told me he
changed Uther's face to

524
00:40:03.828 --> 00:40:08.264
resemble your husband.
the Duke of Cornwall.

525
00:40:08.299 --> 00:40:09.833
That's not possible.

526
00:40:09.867 --> 00:40:14.771
No. it's not. But
I believe it happened.

527
00:40:14.805 --> 00:40:16.472
There was a
moment. when I looked at

528
00:40:16.507 --> 00:40:22.412
him. that I saw another.

529
00:40:27.117 --> 00:40:31.254
I saw Uther.

530
00:40:31.288 --> 00:40:32.655
I don't understand.

531
00:40:32.690 --> 00:40:35.925
How did you then come
to be Uther's wife?

532
00:40:35.960 --> 00:40:38.228
That night that
Uther was with me. his

533
00:40:38.262 --> 00:40:40.263
forces killed the Duke.

534
00:40:40.297 --> 00:40:44.100
The vanquishing warlord
can claim the victim's wife.

535
00:40:44.134 --> 00:40:45.935
I was lucky to live.

536
00:40:45.970 --> 00:40:49.372
But you were
pregnant with me.

537
00:40:49.406 --> 00:40:51.107
You gave me up.

538
00:40:51.141 --> 00:40:53.810
Merlin tore
you from my arms.

539
00:40:53.844 --> 00:40:56.145
Didn't you
ever think of me?

540
00:40:56.180 --> 00:40:58.815
You were my first
thought each morning.

541
00:40:58.849 --> 00:41:03.319
I studied every boy's
face. hoping for you.

542
00:41:03.354 --> 00:41:07.924
I was forbidden
to search for you.

543
00:41:07.958 --> 00:41:11.728
I'm so sorry.

544
00:41:20.371 --> 00:41:25.575
Arthur. You all right?

545
00:41:25.609 --> 00:41:28.111
Yes.

546
00:41:28.145 --> 00:41:32.548
What was she like?
How was it?

547
00:41:32.583 --> 00:41:35.151
Fine.

548
00:41:35.185 --> 00:41:39.956
That's it?

549
00:41:39.990 --> 00:41:42.325
Come on.
let's explore.

550
00:41:45.162 --> 00:41:47.463
Let's look up here. Come on.

551
00:42:01.612 --> 00:42:04.380
Here. look at this.

552
00:42:09.887 --> 00:42:16.426
Magnus Quintus built this
fort in the sixth year of

553
00:42:16.460 --> 00:42:22.398
the reign of the Emperor
Valentinio the Second.

554
00:42:22.433 --> 00:42:26.669
He who has begun has
the work half done.

555
00:42:26.704 --> 00:42:28.137
You wouldn't say that if you
saw the state of the place now.

556
00:42:28.172 --> 00:42:30.540
Think of what it must
have been like back then.

557
00:42:30.574 --> 00:42:32.842
Or what
it can be again.

558
00:42:32.876 --> 00:42:34.344
Have you been
following us?

559
00:42:34.378 --> 00:42:36.746
Merlin's instructions.

560
00:42:36.780 --> 00:42:38.748
I'm to keep you safe.

561
00:42:38.782 --> 00:42:41.417
Keep me safe or
make sure I don't leave?

562
00:42:41.452 --> 00:42:42.885
Bit of both.

563
00:42:42.920 --> 00:42:44.487
What if I
make a run for it?

564
00:42:44.521 --> 00:42:46.055
Why would you?
You've got everything here.

565
00:42:46.090 --> 00:42:48.358
There's so much-potential.

566
00:42:48.392 --> 00:42:49.559
You sound like Merlin.

567
00:42:49.593 --> 00:42:50.860
I believe
in what he's doing.

568
00:42:50.894 --> 00:42:53.396
Why he brought you here.

569
00:42:53.430 --> 00:42:54.564
So you followed
him blindly even though

570
00:42:54.598 --> 00:42:56.099
you hadn't met me.

571
00:42:56.133 --> 00:42:57.500
No. not blindly.

572
00:42:57.534 --> 00:42:59.268
Some of us have always
felt it's not enough just

573
00:42:59.303 --> 00:43:01.971
to fight; there has to be
a cause worth fighting for.

574
00:43:02.006 --> 00:43:04.073
Merlin's told us what's
possible. what can be

575
00:43:04.108 --> 00:43:09.012
built here with you and
your breed of king.

576
00:43:09.046 --> 00:43:13.883
How do I
become that overnight?

577
00:43:13.917 --> 00:43:17.787
Trust your instincts.

578
00:43:17.821 --> 00:43:19.856
My instincts
aren't that of a king.

579
00:43:19.890 --> 00:43:22.925
What if they are
and you just don't know it yet?

580
00:44:38.836 --> 00:44:44.707
<i>Who is</i>
<i>she? Who is she?</i>

581
00:44:44.741 --> 00:44:46.642
Who is she? Who is she?

582
00:44:46.677 --> 00:44:48.044
What're you doing?!

583
00:44:48.078 --> 00:44:49.045
Who is she?

584
00:44:49.079 --> 00:44:50.279
I don't know!

585
00:44:50.314 --> 00:44:53.783
Arthur!
You'd better see this.

586
00:45:11.869 --> 00:45:14.770
This is all for you.

587
00:45:14.805 --> 00:45:19.375
God help me.

588
00:45:19.409 --> 00:45:21.144
What do we do now?

589
00:45:21.178 --> 00:45:24.881
Show no fear.
Speak boldly.

590
00:45:24.915 --> 00:45:26.215
Answer them as their king.

591
00:45:26.250 --> 00:45:27.750
Nothing to
worry about. right?

592
00:45:27.784 --> 00:45:29.452
I mean. you've had visions.
I'm going to be king.

593
00:45:29.486 --> 00:45:30.820
Everything's going to be fine.
It's fate. It's guaranteed.

594
00:45:30.854 --> 00:45:32.355
- No.
- No?

595
00:45:32.389 --> 00:45:33.756
If you die.
the visions will change.

596
00:45:33.790 --> 00:45:35.358
Fate can go begging.

597
00:45:35.392 --> 00:45:38.227
Destiny has to be won.

598
00:46:39.590 --> 00:46:41.157
Nothing can
ever be the same after

599
00:46:41.191 --> 00:46:43.960
this moment. Arthur.

600
00:46:43.994 --> 00:46:47.196
Leave now and
salvage your life.

601
00:46:47.231 --> 00:46:51.000
Stay. and you'll
lose everything.

602
00:46:58.308 --> 00:47:00.543
You're outnumbered.

603
00:47:00.577 --> 00:47:05.114
Don't be a sorcerer's
figurehead. Go home.

604
00:47:15.359 --> 00:47:17.660
Speak. y'beardless bastard!

605
00:47:24.334 --> 00:47:27.203
You stand in my
hall in my realm and you

606
00:47:27.237 --> 00:47:29.772
will show me respect!

607
00:47:29.806 --> 00:47:31.574
I am the true
and legitimate heir

608
00:47:31.608 --> 00:47:33.142
to Uther's throne.

609
00:47:33.176 --> 00:47:34.410
And you will pledge your
allegiance to me.

610
00:47:34.444 --> 00:47:35.678
or suffer for it.

611
00:47:35.712 --> 00:47:39.482
Understand that.
y'bearded fool?

612
00:47:39.516 --> 00:47:43.486
I'm sorry.

613
00:47:43.520 --> 00:47:45.588
Bring him in.

614
00:47:57.668 --> 00:48:01.937
That's my son. My eldest son.

615
00:48:01.972 --> 00:48:06.442
And you killed him.

616
00:48:06.476 --> 00:48:09.745
There were two outriders
in the woods that day.

617
00:48:09.780 --> 00:48:14.650
The other one saw it all.

618
00:48:20.390 --> 00:48:26.128
He attacked me.

619
00:48:42.312 --> 00:48:45.014
No! You bastard!

620
00:48:54.658 --> 00:48:56.225
Shh. shh.

621
00:48:56.259 --> 00:48:59.261
This stops nothing-

622
00:48:59.296 --> 00:49:04.133
I'm not a monster.
Five dawns I'll give you.

623
00:49:04.167 --> 00:49:08.738
Five dawns for him to
grieve and then be gone.

624
00:49:08.772 --> 00:49:12.508
But if you don't leave.
there will be more slaughter.

625
00:49:17.247 --> 00:49:18.214
Stop him!

626
00:49:18.248 --> 00:49:22.618
Shh. shh.

627
00:49:22.652 --> 00:49:23.686
Stop him! Stop
him! Stop him! Stop-

628
00:49:23.720 --> 00:49:27.523
I'm sorry-I'm sorry-

629
00:49:27.557 --> 00:49:31.327
Merlin. what have
you done to me? Get off!

630
00:49:31.361 --> 00:49:34.864
What have you done to me?

631
00:49:41.570 --> 00:49:45.170
== sync. corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> ==

631
00:49:46.305 --> 00:50:46.302
